      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tools): add encoding parameter to read tool for non-UTF-8 files",
        "body": "> AI-assisted (Claude). All behavior proof below was produced and verified by a human-run command in a real local checkout using OpenClaw CLI.\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Problem:** The read tool always decodes files as UTF-8, causing garbled text (mojibake) when reading GBK-encoded files on Chinese Windows.\n- **Why now:** Chinese Windows users commonly have GBK-encoded text files. The read tool produces garbled output instead of readable text.\n- **Outcome:** Add an optional `encoding` parameter to the read tool schema. Users can specify file encoding (e.g. \"gbk\", \"gb2312\", \"shift_jis\"). Default is \"utf-8\". Use \"auto\" to auto-detect BOM or default to utf-8. Uses `TextDecoder` for non-UTF-8 encodings.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #92664\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Read tool displays garbled text when reading GBK-encoded files on Chinese Windows.\n- **Real environment tested:** Windows 10, Node.js v22.22.3, OpenClaw latest main, local checkout with the patch applied.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran regression tests via `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/sessions/tools/read.test.ts`.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Test output:\n  ```\n  ✓ read tool > reads GBK-encoded files with explicit encoding (regression #92664)\n  ✓ read tool > reads UTF-8 files by default\n  Tests 6 passed (6)\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix:** GBK-encoded files are correctly decoded when `encoding: \"gbk\"` is specified. UTF-8 files work as before.\n- **Before evidence:** Same test with the fix reverted shows garbled output for GBK-encoded files.\n- **What was not tested:** Live read tool call with real GBK file on Chinese Windows.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/sessions/tools/read.test.ts` — 6/6 passed\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- **userVisible:** Yes (read tool now supports encoding parameter)\n- **configEnvMigration:** No\n- **securityAuthNetwork:** No\n- **Mitigation:** Default encoding is \"utf-8\", backward compatible.\n",
